# This app already reads the platform-injected PORT via entrypoint.sh
# (java --server.port=$PORT), so nothing port-related is needed here.
#
# If you drop that entrypoint mapping, Spring still honours the SERVER_PORT env
# natively — then set it to the SAME value as app.yaml's `port`:
#   SERVER_PORT=8080
#
# Real secrets (DATABASE_URL, etc.) go in the app's apps/spring-hello/.env on
# the VPS, which is chmod 600 and gitignored — never commit them.
